  "title": "Resident Physician (Prison Medical Officer)",
  "description": "<p>The Resident Physician will be appointed as a Prison Medical Officer to render clinical services in the Singapore Prisons Service.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Responsibilities</u></p>\n<p>The scope of work involves practicing acute care, chronic disease management and specialized duties associated with the operational concerns of the Singapore Prisons Service.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Requirements</u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Basic medical degree registered with the Singapore Medical Council ;</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience as Medical Officer or equivalent;</li>\n  <li>Prior experiences delivering primary care, women's care or having worked in similar secured setting / facility would be an added advantage.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><u>What we offer</u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Opportunities for further training and upgrading of qualifications</li>\n  <li>Regular work hours</li>\n  <li>Competitive remuneration package that commensurate with relevant experiences, credentials and qualifications</li>\n</ol>",
